00:00:55,290 --> 00:00:57,219
It's the 80th anniversary of Superman

24
00:00:57,220 --> 00:00:58,430
and the origin of Krypton,

25
00:00:58,460 --> 00:00:59,959
<i>and as an actor and fan,</i>

26
00:00:59,960 --> 00:01:02,790
I couldn't be more excited to
be part of this next chapter.

27
00:01:03,630 --> 00:01:08,630
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28
00:01:08,640 --> 00:01:10,239
<i>One of the things that I wanted to do</i>

29
00:01:10,240 --> 00:01:12,239
<i>with "Man of Steel" was to emphasize</i>

30
00:01:12,240 --> 00:01:14,570
the fact that Superman was an alien,

31
00:01:14,580 --> 00:01:18,200
and so I fought very hard
to have an opening segment

32
00:01:18,240 --> 00:01:19,479
<i>take place on Krypton</i>

33
00:01:19,480 --> 00:01:22,510
<i>and to depict it as a truly alien world.</i>

34
00:01:22,520 --> 00:01:23,919
So while I was working on that film,

35
00:01:23,920 --> 00:01:25,419
<i>I thought a lot about</i>

36
00:01:25,420 --> 00:01:27,389
<i>how we could take things further,</i>

37
00:01:27,390 --> 00:01:29,560
<i>and I approached Geoff Johns.</i>

38
00:01:29,620 --> 00:01:31,320
<i>It really started with a conversation</i>

39
00:01:31,330 --> 00:01:32,420
when David came to me and said,

40
00:01:32,430 --> 00:01:33,459
"Hey, I think I have an idea

41
00:01:33,460 --> 00:01:34,529
about a story on Krypton,"

42
00:01:34,530 --> 00:01:37,280
<i>how the House of El became this symbol</i>

43
00:01:37,310 --> 00:01:38,660
<i>of hope and optimism.</i>

44
00:01:38,670 --> 00:01:40,629
It's about this character, Seg,

45
00:01:40,630 --> 00:01:42,599
<i>who's the grandfather of Superman,</i>

46
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:45,269
and it would take place
about 200 years before

47
00:01:45,270 --> 00:01:46,900
<i>Superman comes to Earth.</i>

48
00:01:46,980 --> 00:01:49,439
Superman came from
a very sophisticated world.

49
00:01:49,440 --> 00:01:51,340
<i>They were very advanced,
but at the same time,</i>

50
00:01:51,350 --> 00:01:53,749
<i>beyond this sort of veneer of harmony,</i>

51
00:01:53,750 --> 00:01:54,810
<i>there was corruption.</i>

52
00:01:54,820 --> 00:01:56,120
<i>There was Machiavellian</i>

53
00:01:56,220 --> 00:01:57,580
politics going on.

54
00:01:57,590 --> 00:01:59,349
<i>I think it's something that speaks to us</i>

55
00:01:59,350 --> 00:02:01,619
<i>in our world today.</i>

56
00:02:01,620 --> 00:02:03,689
I think that's the big draw
to "Krypton,"

57
00:02:03,690 --> 00:02:06,180
<i>to dive deeply into what Krypton is.</i>

58
00:02:06,420 --> 00:02:08,759
<i>What was it like
before Superman, as a baby,</i>

59
00:02:08,760 --> 00:02:11,560
<i>left that world
and the world was destroyed?</i>

60
00:02:12,770 --> 00:02:14,730
<i>[MELANCHOLY PIANO MUSIC]</i>

61
00:02:14,740 --> 00:02:16,299
<i>The Krypton of our show</i>

62
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:19,120
is a planet that is late
in its life cycle,

63
00:02:19,240 --> 00:02:20,870
<i>and resources are so limited</i>

64
00:02:20,880 --> 00:02:22,639
<i>that there are only
a certain amount of people</i>

65
00:02:22,640 --> 00:02:24,679
<i>that the government seems to care about.</i>

66
00:02:24,680 --> 00:02:27,349
The society's divided by class.

67
00:02:27,350 --> 00:02:28,879
It's a theocracy.

68
00:02:28,880 --> 00:02:32,480
<i>There's an authoritarian,
religious ruler.</i>

69
00:02:32,490 --> 00:02:36,719
Rao's blessings are bountiful
but not unlimited.

70
00:02:36,720 --> 00:02:39,589
Only his wrath is.

71
00:02:39,590 --> 00:02:41,980
Seg is a son of the House of El,

72
00:02:42,020 --> 00:02:44,629
which has had its once proud legacy

73
00:02:44,630 --> 00:02:46,050
<i>ripped from them</i>

74
00:02:46,080 --> 00:02:47,940
<i>when Seg's grandfather, Val-El,</i>

75
00:02:47,980 --> 00:02:49,230
<i>commits heresy by saying</i>

76
00:02:49,240 --> 00:02:52,600
<i>that there is something out there
other than Kryptonians.</i>

77
00:02:52,610 --> 00:02:55,209
For rebelling against
the lawful authority

78
00:02:55,210 --> 00:02:57,279
of the Holy Sovereignty of His Eminence,

79
00:02:57,280 --> 00:03:00,849
you are hereby sentenced to death!

80
00:03:00,850 --> 00:03:02,320
When we pick up our story,

81
00:03:02,340 --> 00:03:04,819
the House of El has been maligned.

82
00:03:04,820 --> 00:03:07,030
<i>The Superman symbol is a mark of shame.</i>

83
00:03:07,060 --> 00:03:10,389
Your family will be stripped
of all rights and privileges!

84
00:03:10,390 --> 00:03:12,859
You are now to be considered rankless!

85
00:03:12,860 --> 00:03:16,159
<i>He grows up rankless
in the rankless district,</i>

86
00:03:16,160 --> 00:03:18,129
which is this crevasse
at the bottom of the city

87
00:03:18,130 --> 00:03:20,199
<i>where people are just sort of piled in</i>

88
00:03:20,200 --> 00:03:22,380
<i>on top of each other.
It's a dog-eat-dog world.</i>

89
00:03:22,460 --> 00:03:24,569
- Move along.
- Hey!

90
00:03:24,570 --> 00:03:26,269
His mind's not right anymore.

91
00:03:26,270 --> 00:03:31,409
Seg's a good kid,
who's very angry at the world.

92
00:03:31,410 --> 00:03:33,279
[GRUNTING]

93
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:37,479
<i>♪ ♪</i>

94
00:03:37,480 --> 00:03:41,090
We didn't want to start Seg
as the finished package.

95
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:43,189
You know, we didn't want him
to be Superman.

96
00:03:43,190 --> 00:03:44,980
<i>We didn't want him to have all of those</i>

97
00:03:45,060 --> 00:03:47,629
<i>core values in place
right from the start.</i>

98
00:03:47,630 --> 00:03:49,150
We wanted that to be the journey,

99
00:03:49,180 --> 00:03:50,859
<i>and we wanted that to be a progression.</i>

100
00:03:50,860 --> 00:03:53,199
What the hell were you thinking, Seg?

101
00:03:53,200 --> 00:03:55,169
Are you gonna uncuff me or what?

102
00:03:55,170 --> 00:03:57,299
I like you this way.

103
00:03:57,300 --> 00:04:00,180
Even though
"Krypton's" very much a story

104
00:04:00,220 --> 00:04:02,609
about the House of El
and the El lineage,

105
00:04:02,610 --> 00:04:04,750
<i>it's also a story about the House of Zod</i>

106
00:04:04,770 --> 00:04:06,209
<i>and the Zod lineage.</i>

107
00:04:06,210 --> 00:04:09,549
Lyta, you are my daughter,
and you are a Zod,

108
00:04:09,550 --> 00:04:12,220
and Zods are not traitors.

109
00:04:12,270 --> 00:04:15,700
<i>Lyta Zod, she's part
of the Military guild.</i>

110
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:17,759
She has this relationship with Seg,

111
00:04:17,760 --> 00:04:19,459
<i>which is not allowed.</i>

112
00:04:19,460 --> 00:04:21,390
<i>She shouldn't be going near a rankless.</i>

113
00:04:21,400 --> 00:04:23,859
So much in our lives we can't control.

114
00:04:23,860 --> 00:04:26,599
But we still get to define ourselves.

115
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:29,200
Seg is someone that she can speak to.

116
00:04:29,260 --> 00:04:30,739
<i>They're really in love, and they have</i>

117
00:04:30,740 --> 00:04:32,200
<i>this really passionate relationship,</i>

118
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:34,509
<i>but they know that it's never gonna last</i>

119
00:04:34,510 --> 00:04:36,779
because they're both bound
to different people.

120
00:04:36,780 --> 00:04:38,540
<i>He's bound to Nyssa.</i>

121
00:04:38,550 --> 00:04:40,409
Nyssa here is yet to
be paired with someone.

122
00:04:40,410 --> 00:04:44,349
As my youngest daughter,
you'll be binding with her.

123
00:04:44,350 --> 00:04:47,249
She's the woman that Seg is bound to.

124
00:04:47,250 --> 00:04:49,789
They don't call it marriage,
they call it a binding.

125
00:04:49,790 --> 00:04:53,559
<i>He takes an immediate disliking
to Nyssa, and she to him.</i>

126
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:56,290
If my father binds you to us,
he is taming you.

127
00:04:56,300 --> 00:04:58,750
Proving that even a dreaded El
can be co-opted

128
00:04:58,760 --> 00:05:00,000
and brought into the fold.

129
00:05:00,150 --> 00:05:02,580
<i>Nyssa-Vex is a junior magistrate</i>

130
00:05:02,590 --> 00:05:04,089
<i>of the Lawmaker's guild.</i>

131
00:05:04,090 --> 00:05:05,650
I think a lot of Nyssa's relationships

132
00:05:05,660 --> 00:05:07,019
are built on an agenda,

133
00:05:07,020 --> 00:05:09,910
<i>and Nyssa sees Seg as a commodity.</i>

134
00:05:09,940 --> 00:05:11,600
Have your secrets, Seg.

135
00:05:11,620 --> 00:05:13,709
I most certainly have mine.

136
00:05:13,710 --> 00:05:17,179
Seg early on in the story
receives a call to action,

137
00:05:17,180 --> 00:05:20,089
and this call reminds him
of the great legacy

138
00:05:20,090 --> 00:05:22,189
<i>of his house, of the acts of courage</i>

139
00:05:22,190 --> 00:05:24,159
<i>and selflessness that are so incredible</i>

140
00:05:24,160 --> 00:05:25,760
<i>that they resound through history,</i>

141
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:26,620
<i>but here's the kicker:</i>

142
00:05:26,700 --> 00:05:29,790
they also resound in the future.

143
00:05:29,810 --> 00:05:31,140
[GRUNTS]

144
00:05:31,170 --> 00:05:32,400
Don't even think about it.

145
00:05:32,550 --> 00:05:33,680
This stranger shows up,

146
00:05:33,830 --> 00:05:35,230
<i>says, "I'm from the future.</i>

147
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:36,799
<i>"I'm from a planet called Earth.</i>

148
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:38,080
<i>"My name is Adam Strange,</i>

149
00:05:38,100 --> 00:05:40,340
<i>and I need your help to save Krypton."</i>

150
00:05:40,420 --> 00:05:42,770
Someone from the future
has come to destroy Krypton.

151
00:05:42,810 --> 00:05:44,090
Why would they do that?

152
00:05:44,110 --> 00:05:45,660
Because where I'm from,
your grandson becomes

153
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:47,420
the greatest hero in the universe.

154
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:49,979
No one on Krypton, including Seg,

155
00:05:49,980 --> 00:05:53,320
has any awareness of Superman
or even Earth at this point,

156
00:05:53,360 --> 00:05:55,480
<i>so Adam is the audience's proxy.</i>

157
00:05:55,540 --> 00:05:57,469
Once this cape is gone, our time's up.

158
00:05:57,470 --> 00:06:00,179
Superman will have been wiped
from existence.

159
00:06:00,180 --> 00:06:02,140
<i>Because he is a time traveler,</i>

160
00:06:02,150 --> 00:06:04,410
he shows that the show
is not just a prequel.

161
00:06:04,420 --> 00:06:07,479
<i>It's a story that is indelibly
linked to the present,</i>

162
00:06:07,480 --> 00:06:09,399
<i>so the events that happen in our show</i>

163
00:06:09,400 --> 00:06:11,519
<i>could change Krypton's ultimate fate.</i>

164
00:06:11,520 --> 00:06:12,819
[BOY YELLS]

165
00:06:12,820 --> 00:06:14,520
This thing that's coming,

166
00:06:14,530 --> 00:06:17,129
it moves... from planet to planet,

167
00:06:17,130 --> 00:06:18,829
<i>conquering civilizations.</i>

168
00:06:18,830 --> 00:06:22,600
<i>Its true name is Brainiac.</i>

169
00:06:25,590 --> 00:06:27,319
Superman was created out of nothing.

170
00:06:27,320 --> 00:06:28,580
<i>There were no superheroes.</i>

171
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:31,320
Superman has been through
everything you can think of.

172
00:06:31,390 --> 00:06:33,810
There's a reason why
Superman still persists.

173
00:06:37,980 --> 00:06:40,210
So, here we are in the Genesis Chamber,

174
00:06:40,240 --> 00:06:41,770
and the cool thing
about the Genesis Chamber

175
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:43,510
<i>is that it's actually
a relatively new part</i>

176
00:06:43,530 --> 00:06:46,480
<i>of the lore introduced in 2014's
"Man of Steel."</i>

177
00:06:46,530 --> 00:06:48,220
And the amazing thing to me as a fan

178
00:06:48,240 --> 00:06:49,630
<i>is that even though this franchise</i>

179
00:06:49,660 --> 00:06:51,180
<i>has been going on for 80 years,</i>

180
00:06:51,210 --> 00:06:52,750
<i>the world of Krypton is so rich</i>

181
00:06:52,770 --> 00:06:54,520
that there's really no end
to the creative

182
00:06:54,540 --> 00:06:56,920
<i>and storytelling possibilities.</i>

183
00:06:58,870 --> 00:07:01,010
<i>There's a lot of characters
that have been introduced</i>

184
00:07:01,030 --> 00:07:02,930
from 1938 to now,

185
00:07:02,950 --> 00:07:04,489
<i>and a lot of them have been forgotten,</i>

186
00:07:04,490 --> 00:07:07,210
<i>but there's a reason why
Superman still persists.</i>

187
00:07:07,260 --> 00:07:08,950
Superman was created out of nothing.

188
00:07:09,010 --> 00:07:10,450
There were no superheroes.

189
00:07:10,510 --> 00:07:13,070
<i>There was just Jerry Siegel
and Joe Shuster</i>

190
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:14,490
<i>in Cleveland, Ohio,</i>

191
00:07:14,530 --> 00:07:17,469
<i>creating an alien character
called Superman.</i>

192
00:07:17,470 --> 00:07:20,580
In 1938, in short,
the world had never been

193
00:07:20,610 --> 00:07:23,579
<i>a scarier or more unjust place.</i>

194
00:07:23,580 --> 00:07:26,579
<i>And at that time,
the world's first superhero</i>

195
00:07:26,580 --> 00:07:29,110
<i>appeared on bookshelves.</i>

196
00:07:29,170 --> 00:07:30,729
<i>I don't think it's a coincidence</i>

197
00:07:30,730 --> 00:07:32,499
that this guy became popular.

198
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:34,400
<i>♪ ♪</i>

199
00:07:34,410 --> 00:07:38,539
He's always that shining
beacon of goodness and courage.

200
00:07:38,540 --> 00:07:40,409
Truth, justice, and the American way...

201
00:07:40,410 --> 00:07:42,579
<i>I mean, these are,
like, spiritual ideas.</i>

202
00:07:42,580 --> 00:07:44,449
<i>These are ideas you can build
a religion around.</i>

203
00:07:44,450 --> 00:07:47,120
Here we have an alien
among us in Superman

204
00:07:47,260 --> 00:07:50,180
<i>who represents the highest
and best qualities</i>

205
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:54,389
<i>of what we like to think of as humanity.</i>

206
00:07:54,390 --> 00:07:56,189
Why has Superman endured for so long?

207
00:07:56,190 --> 00:07:58,590
It's because those themes are undying,

208
00:07:58,600 --> 00:07:59,900
<i>and so is he.</i>

209
00:08:01,670 --> 00:08:04,569
Superman has been through
just about everything

210
00:08:04,570 --> 00:08:06,869
<i>you can think of... 52 universes,</i>

211
00:08:06,870 --> 00:08:09,809
<i>evil versions of himself,
bizarro versions of himself.</i>

212
00:08:09,810 --> 00:08:11,670
<i>He died, very famously.</i>

213
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:13,800
Superman kind of is so well known

214
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:16,110
and so well documented... in animation,

215
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:17,509
<i>in film, in television,</i>

216
00:08:17,510 --> 00:08:18,780
<i>in comics.</i>

217
00:08:18,860 --> 00:08:21,120
First connection I had
to Superman growing up

218
00:08:21,270 --> 00:08:23,439
<i>was the day I read
my first "Superman" comic.</i>

219
00:08:23,440 --> 00:08:25,100
<i>It kind of taught you</i>

220
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:26,539
<i>you could do almost anything you wanted.</i>

221
00:08:26,540 --> 00:08:28,400
<i>If he could, why couldn't I?</i>

222
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:31,540
My very first connection
was the Max and Dave Fleischer

223
00:08:31,550 --> 00:08:33,040
<i>"Superman" cartoons</i>

224
00:08:33,080 --> 00:08:35,710
<i>that I saw when I was very, very young.</i>

225
00:08:35,720 --> 00:08:39,030
They were done on a really
elaborate scale for cartoons.

226
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:41,850
<i>They were very realistic
and very cinematic.</i>

227
00:08:41,860 --> 00:08:43,589
I am and always will be a fan

228
00:08:43,590 --> 00:08:46,329
of the original TV series,
"Adventures of Superman,"

229
00:08:46,330 --> 00:08:47,960
<i>with George Reeves, 'cause that's what</i>

230
00:08:47,980 --> 00:08:49,140
<i>I grew up with as a kid.</i>

231
00:08:49,280 --> 00:08:50,629
Your aim is bad, Luigi.

232
00:08:50,630 --> 00:08:52,629
The first Superman movie
with Christopher Reeve

233
00:08:52,630 --> 00:08:56,369
<i>really embraced
the Superman I grew up with.</i>

234
00:08:56,370 --> 00:08:58,940
<i>I read the script, and quite honestly,</i>

235
00:08:58,960 --> 00:09:00,709
<i>it was missing the humanity,</i>

236
00:09:00,710 --> 00:09:04,340
<i>its sense of reality.</i>

237
00:09:04,350 --> 00:09:07,220
<i>I decided to do it
if they'd let me do a rewrite,</i>

238
00:09:07,300 --> 00:09:09,750
and the reason I would do it
